  "prompt": "What are the best documentary websites?",
  "response": "There are several reputable websites where you can watch a wide variety of documentaries. Here are some of the best ones:\n\n1. **CuriosityStream**:\n   - CuriosityStream offers a vast collection of high-quality documentaries on science, history, nature, and more. It's founded by John Hendricks, the founder of the Discovery Channel.\n\n2. **Netflix**:\n   - Netflix has an extensive library of documentaries, ranging from true crime to nature and social issues. Some popular documentary series include \"Making a Murderer\" and \"Our Planet.\"\n\n3. **Kanopy**:\n   - Kanopy is a streaming service that offers a wide range of documentaries, often with a focus on social issues, arts, and education. It's free to use with a library card from participating libraries.\n\n4. **PBS Documentaries**:\n   - PBS offers a variety of acclaimed documentaries on their website, covering topics such as history, science, and culture. You can stream many of these for free.\n\n5. **DocuBay**:\n   - DocuBay is a specialized documentary streaming platform that offers a diverse range of high-quality documentaries across genres like adventure, crime, history, and more.\n\n6. **YouTube**:\n   - YouTube hosts a plethora of free documentaries from various creators and established channels like National Geographic and BBC. The quality and reliability can vary, so it's good to check the source.\n\n7. **Top Documentary Films**:\n   - This website offers a wide selection of documentaries that you can stream for free. It covers a variety of topics, and while some documentaries may be less professionally produced, you can find some gems.\n\n8. **Vimeo**:\n   - Vimeo has a curated selection of documentaries, often from independent filmmakers. You might need to pay for some, but there are also many available for free.\n\n9. **Amazon Prime Video**:\n   - Amazon Prime Video offers a robust selection of documentaries, including exclusive content. You can find everything from historical documentaries to contemporary social issues.\n\n10. **Drafthouse Films**:\n    - Drafthouse Films, a part of the Alamo Drafthouse Cinema, offers unique and critically acclaimed documentaries. You can rent or buy these films on their website.\n\nWhen choosing a documentary, consider the source and reviews to ensure you're getting high-quality and accurate information. Enjoy your documentary watching!",
